# NunezDev — example environment variables.
# Copy to .env.local and fill in real values. Anything prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_
# is exposed to the browser at build time, so only put non-secret values here.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Search engine site-verification codes (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Both vars only matter if you're using the "HTML meta tag" verification
# method. If empty, no meta tag is rendered (which is the correct behavior
# when verification happens elsewhere — see below). Don't fill in unless
# the method you used actually requires a meta tag.

# Google: ONLY needed if your GSC property is a "URL prefix" property
#   verified via the HTML tag method. If your property is a Domain
#   property (verified via a DNS TXT record at your registrar), leave
#   this empty — your site is already verified at the DNS layer.
#   GSC: https://search.google.com/search-console
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=

# Bing: ONLY needed if you verified Bing Webmaster Tools via the
#   "Meta tag" method. If you imported the site from Google Search
#   Console (Bing inherits GSC's verification) or verified via DNS,
#   leave this empty.
#   Bing Webmaster: https://www.bing.com/webmasters
NEXT_PUBLIC_BING_VERIFICATION=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Turnstile — spam protection on public forms
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by /api/contact and /api/appointments to block bot submissions.
# Free tier covers up to 1M requests/month. If BOTH are unset, the widget
# is hidden and server-side verification is skipped (forms still work).
#
# Set up at https://dash.cloudflare.com/?to=/:account/turnstile
#   1. Create a site (managed challenge, invisible)
#   2. Add hostname: www.nunezdev.com (and nunezdev.com if no redirect)
#   3. Copy the Site Key into NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY (client-facing)
#   4. Copy the Secret Key into TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY (server-only)
NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=
